Trump&#39;s new chief of staff plans to cut back on the president&#39;s media diet
Many had tried before him and had always failed.
Maybe John F. Kelly can actually do it.
If so, it will be the first.
Politico reported that the new White House chief of staff plans to limit the flow of information about President Trump -- including television news coverage -- in hopes of keeping Trump afloat.
Here is part of reporter Josh Dawsey&#39;s report:
“When new White House Chief of Staff John F. Kelly met with staff on his first day in office, he outlined a key problem in the Trump White House that he intends to fix: the misinformation that is getting into the hands of the president.
