According to the UN, Afghan democracy relies on women in politics
Elections can only be credible if all members of society, including women, participate, the UN representative in Afghanistan said on Wednesday.
Nicholas Haysom, a senior official at the UN Assistance Mission, said hundreds of women are participating in local council elections, three women are running for vice president and more than 30 percent of newly registered voters are women.
&quot;The role of women cannot be overlooked,&quot; he said in a statement on Wednesday.
Elections can only be fully representative and credible if women participate in them, as well as in all the related processes that are connected to the elections.
Local and presidential elections in Afghanistan take place on April 5.
The Taliban have issued several threats against the electoral process, which puts international fighting on the back burner.
In this year&#39;s elections, for the first time ever, one democratically elected government peacefully hands over its power to the next government.
Haysom said a strong role for women will strengthen Afghanistan&#39;s democracy.
Afghanistan&#39;s Independent Electoral Commission said that out of a total of 3.6 million registered voters, 1.2 million were women.
The unique brewery is brewing beer again.
For a good beer at the resurrected brewery.
The enthusiasm and honesty of the new owners brought the brewery in Lobč u Mšena back to life a few years ago.
The brewery, mentioned for the first time already in 1586, has a Renaissance core and was converted to steam engine operation in the nineteenth century.
The boom years followed, when the brewery was famous mainly for its dark beers.
Unfortunately, production was stopped during the Second World War and the brewery was nationalized in 1984.
Since then, the buildings have served as a state farm.
The work of destruction was completed by the owners of the brewery after 1989.
The abandoned site was devastated and dismantled for construction material.
In 2007, however, new hope dawned in the form of new owners, architects Jana and Pavel Prouzová.
They began to repair the buildings with maximum respect for the spirit of the building and every detail.
They carefully devoted themselves to the study of archival materials, trying to preserve the original materials and building elements.
The brewery thus has the same appearance as in the nineteenth century, when its golden era started.
Their work was recognized by the declaration of the brewery as a cultural monument by the Ministry of Culture, and the building also became part of the European Industrial Heritage Trails.
In 2015, they ceremonially renewed the tradition of brewing beer.
If you want to taste great Lobeč beer in the picturesque landscape of the Kokořín region, visit the tap on the premises of the brewery.
When brewing beer here, they use Kokořín water springing from a protected landscape area, malt from Lobeč fields and Žatec hops.
In the taproom, you can taste traditional light lager, as well as dark beers and specials.
And don&#39;t miss the tour of the brewery, it takes place on Saturday and Sunday at noon and half past two.
The biggest artillery fortress of Czechoslovakia?
One of the largest fortresses of its type on a global scale?
Such a unique structure should have been the Stachelberg fortress between Trutnov and Žacléř, on the top of the terrain ridge above the village of Babí.
Originally, it was supposed to consist of up to twelve bunkers connected by an extensive underground.
Here was to be the headquarters, barracks, ammunition and material stores, power plant, engine room and hospital.
But the construction was ended by the Munich Agreement.
In less than a year, a single massive reinforced concrete bunker was built and the underground spaces were broken out.
Thanks to the enthusiasts from the Stachelberg Association, who started to reconstruct the unique building in the early nineties, you too can take a look.
The underground is already 75 percent accessible!
In addition to the TS 73 infantry cabin with an exhibition and underground, the area also includes an armed object of light fortification, as well as two infantry cabins under construction, trenches and the Fortified Trutnovsko educational trail.
Refreshments, a cozy gazebo and breathtaking views of the countryside guaranteed!
